                            <comment id="13662228" author="beamerblvd" created="Mon, 20 May 2013 18:11:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed, the TLD is incorrect, and the &lt;tt&gt;logger&lt;/tt&gt; attribute should be used instead, not the &lt;tt&gt;value&lt;/tt&gt; attribute, which doesn&apos;t actually exist. I&apos;ll get this fixed shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13663694" author="beamerblvd" created="Wed, 22 May 2013 02:21:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note: The maven-taglib-plugin is &lt;em&gt;supposed&lt;/em&gt; to flag issues like this. However, the generated report is all green checkboxes. It does not flag the fact that the attribute does not have a setter. I have filed &lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.openmindlab.com/browse/MAVENTAGLIB-16&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://jira.openmindlab.com/browse/MAVENTAGLIB-16&lt;/a&gt; about this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, I have filed a featured request for the maven-taglib-plugin to be able to run it at compile time and fail the build if validation fails. &lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.openmindlab.com/browse/MAVENTAGLIB-17&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://jira.openmindlab.com/browse/MAVENTAGLIB-17&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13663696" author="beamerblvd" created="Wed, 22 May 2013 02:30:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolved with r1485032. Please verify and close.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
